Property.Name: QueryScript
Property.Value: SELECT u.Id, u.FirstName, u.LastName, u.Email, u.PhoneNumber, u.Age FROM [identity].[AspNetUsers] u

Property.Name: QueryScript
Property.Value: SELECT a.[Id], a.[JobId] ,a.[Status] ,a.[AppliedAt] ,j.Title AS JobTitle ,j.Description AS JobDescription ,a.[StatusChangedAt] ,j.[EmployerId] ,u.FirstName + ' ' + u.LastName AS EmployeeFullName ,j.CreatedAt AS JobCreatedAt FROM [zaposlime].[Application] a LEFT JOIN [zaposlime].[Job] j ON J.Id = a.JobId LEFT JOIN [identity].[AspNetUsers] u ON a.[EmployeeId] = u.Id

Property.Name: QueryScript
Property.Value: SELECT j.Id, j.Title, j.Description, j.NumberOfWorkers, j.EmployerId, j.CityId, j.CreatedAt, u.FirstName + ' ' + u.LastName AS EmployerFullName, c.Name AS CityName FROM [zaposlime].[Job] j LEFT JOIN [identity].[AspNetUsers] u ON u.Id = j.EmployerId LEFT JOIN [zaposlime].[City] c ON c.Id = j.CityId

Property.Name: QueryScript
Property.Value: SELECT a.Id, a.EmployeeId, a.JobId, a.Status, j.Title AS JobTitle, j.Description AS JobDescription, u.FirstName + ' ' + u.LastName AS EmployerFullName, a.AppliedAt, j.CreatedAt AS JobCreatedAt FROM [zaposlime].[Application] a LEFT JOIN [zaposlime].[Job] j ON a.JobId = j.Id LEFT JOIN [identity].[AspNetUsers] u ON j.EmployerId = u.Id
